  "standardBio": "Staticat, titled among keepers as “Spirewind Rider,” carries sudden freedom in every movement. Native to Stormspire Peaks, the species crackles through ozone and kite-silk, leaving traces that other Riftlings can follow like soft maps. Wild groups form loose bonds rather than rigid packs; a curious individual may become the emotional center of a small hearthline. They eat Stormbud eagerly and dislike food that smells of neglect or spoilage. Ancient keepers carved Staticat silhouettes into travel stones, believing the species guided the lost. Modern hatcheries record them as reliable companions; their social intelligence tuned to group moods makes training feel like conversation. Their signature ability, Staticat's Static Bolt, reflects a life shaped by Stormspire Peaks more than by arena ambition. Collectors sometimes treat them as ornaments. Wild Staticats are social strategists, not decorations. Young Staticats practice Staticat's Static Bolt as play long before they understand battle. Adults teach by demonstration: where to rest, what to avoid, how to share warmth or shade.",
  "fullLore": "Staticats first condensed from residual skyfracture along the living edges of Stormspire Peaks after early Rift fractures cooled into weather. Their eggs appear where ozone and kite-silk gathers into stillness—never in the loudest danger, always in the pocket of calm beside it. Early surveyors mistook them for ambient phenomena until a Staticat returned a dropped lantern, carefully, as if returning a promise.\n\nIn ancient eras, regional peoples treated Staticats as omen-bearers rather than pets. Carvings show them walking ahead of caravans, pausing at unstable ground, and curling around children during ashfall or fog. The species was never “tamed” in the old sense; it chose. That choice culture survives in modern Riftkeeper etiquette: you do not yank a Staticat into a bond. You invite, wait, and keep the invitation honest.\n\nModern history is quieter and more practical. Hatcheries map Staticat care cycles with the same seriousness given to rare lines, because common does not mean shallow. Stormspire Peaks still holds wild populations that trade soft greetings with passerby pets. After major Rift events, Staticats often appear first at recovery centers—not as heroes, but as inventory clerks of comfort, counting who is cold, hungry, or afraid.\n\nNatural behavior is curious at the core and adaptable at the edges. They are four-footed and sure on uneven ground, companion-sized, easy to cradle, and communicate through harmonic hums. Socially, they prefer small trusted circles; strangers are assessed by scent, posture, and whether a keeper’s voice stays kind under stress. Intelligence presents as social intelligence tuned to group moods. They sleep in elevated shelves and prefer weather that matches their affinity’s comfort band.\n\nEcologically, Staticats act as trail markers within Stormspire Peaks. Allies often include Commonspark and Peakibex; rivalries with Radiantkit and Auralynx are usually about nesting space or shiny refuse, not blood feuds. Predators are rare—most threats come from collapsing terrain and careless machines rather than jaws.\n\nCulture around them is affectionate and slightly superstitious. Children in border camps still leave a scrap of Stormbud on windowsills when Staticat silhouettes pass at dusk. Collectors prize unusual cosmetics, yet marketplace notes remind buyers that verified care history matters more than glitter. The common misunderstanding remains: Collectors sometimes treat them as ornaments. Wild Staticats are social strategists, not decorations. The hidden truth keepers debate in soft rooms is simpler and stranger: When deeply bonded, a Staticat shares short dream-images of places it has never physically visited.\n\nFrom egg to evolved form, their life story stays continuous. Eggs look like glazed stones veined with storm light. Hatchlings are clumsy with sincerity; adults become specialists of place; evolved stages sharpen instinct without erasing childhood habits. Battle tendencies favor swift harassment, and evolution philosophy insists transformation should answer lived experience—not fashion.\n\nFor Riftkeepers, a Staticat is a living chapter of Stormspire Peaks. Feed it Stormbud, respect its curious tempo, and it will teach you the region’s quieter grammar: which winds lie, which stones remember, which silences are safe. Personal quests often begin with a shell symbol, a remembered scent, or a dream of a door that only opens when the bond is honest. That is the Staticat bargain—not destiny sold at rarity price, but a life that continues because you showed up.",
